A little over four years ago, I bravely took a leap of faith and stepped out of my comfort zone to launch the inaugural BLEXIT chapter in North Carolina. Little did I know, my efforts would catch the attention of Candace Owens, who would eventually hire me (alongside @gmflorio) as the organization's first official employee. Today, BLEXIT has grown into a thriving movement, boasting over 14,000 volunteers, 160+ leaders, and more than 60,000 dedicated supporters.

It's been an incredibly humbling experience to witness the profound impact BLEXIT has had in such a short time. With @blexitamerica now being powered by @turningpointusa (TPUSA), we're ready to take things to the next level. I’ve officially accepted the role of Director of BLEXIT Programming with TPUSA. In this capacity, I'll be working closely with TPUSA's Faith team to advance the missions of BLEXIT and TPUSA. 

As I embark on this new chapter, I'm filled with a sense of optimism and purpose. I'm confident that by putting our faith in God, we can accomplish great things together. Let's roll up our sleeves and get to work!

P.S. if you are being called to take a leap of faith, DO IT. “You miss every shot you don’t take.” -Wayne Gretzky #TPUSA #BLEXIT

This was undoubtedly a defining moment for BLEXIT/TPUSA. After our original venue canceled with less than three days to go, it would have been easier to just give up. Trying to find a venue on such short notice for this type of show is nearly impossible, right? Nope. Everything is possible because we live in the GREATEST country on earth—a country where your work ethic, not your skin color, determines your success. While the left celebrated, thinking they had won, and some others wondered if we should let it go, I told my team that we would not stop. We know that God is still in the blessing business, and I never lost faith, not even for a single second, that we could get this done. We ran around the streets of New York until a venue said yes. Even after 100+ said no, we kept going until we found that "yes."

So, on this #Juneteenth, I hope this sends a message to the left that Black people are not victims. Just like everyone else, if you put your mind to it, you can accomplish it. WE DID IT!

As we wrap up 2023, our faith in God remains. ✝️

Take some time today to reflect on your faith journey this year. Has your faith increased? If it hasn’t, why?
Do not let the Left tell you otherwise.

Since 2018, I’ve been at this, and it never gets old. Admittedly, I don’t spend a lot of time reflecting, but I took a moment to do so after our latest BLEXIT Leadership Conference, and I’m just so incredibly proud of what we’ve built. There is no other group doing what BLEXIT is doing, nor making the impact that BLEXIT is making in minority America. We are leading the way! Our leaders are leading the way! 

I’m incredibly thankful for the support of Turning Point USA! Let’s make 2024 even better. 🔥🇺🇸
